            "ratingValue": "5",
            "bestRating": "5",
            "worstRating": "1"
          },
          "reviewBody": "Hi, Thanks for the opportunity.  The Observatory session was very nice. I have noticed that my kid and his friends in the table was not interact with each other. If the talkative and silent kids mingled in the class will help the silent kids to improve. It's just a suggestion. Once again thanks for the session.",
          "publisher": {
            "@type": "Organization",
            "name": "Yellow Slate"
          }
        },
        {
          "@type": "Review",
          "itemReviewed": {
            "@type": "School",
            "name": "Anan International School - Kovilpalayam"
          },
          "author": {
            "@type": "Person",
            "name": "Kousalya Ramesh"
          },
          "datePublished": "2024-07-26",
          "reviewRating": {
            "@type": "Rating",
            "ratingValue": "4",
            "bestRating": "5",
            "worstRating": "1"
          },
          "reviewBody": "We are glad that there is an opportunity for parents to observe how children make use of the opportunities provided by the school and how well they interact and engage with their peers and staff. During the observatory session, we participated in our child's Western dance class. We were pleased to see how our child responds to and follows the instructions given in the dance class.\n\nOne suggestion for improvement is to frequently shuffle the children's order during the class so that each child can receive equal attention from the trainer. Please disregard this suggestion if it is already being practiced.",
          "publisher": {
            "@type": "Organization",
            "name": "Yellow Slate"
          }
